article.description:
J.R. Bremer scored a career-high 25 points, and
Antoine Walker had 22 points, 12 assists and eight rebounds Friday
night as the Celtics spoiled Dennis Johnson's return to Boston with
a 83-72 victory over the Los Angeles Clippers.
article.headline: Bremer scored a career-high 25 points for Boston
article.linkText: Celtics spoil Johnson's coaching return to Boston
article.story:
BOSTON (AP) -- Dennis Johnson had little opportunity to enjoy his return to Boston.
 
Bremer
The former Celtics star came back as the coach of the Clippers on Friday night and guided Los Angeles to its eighth consecutive loss. J.R. Bremer scored a career-high 25 points, and Antoine Walker had 22 points, 12 assists and eight rebounds in Boston's 83-72 victory. Johnson received a standing ovation when he was introduced before the game. But the emotional reunion turned bizarre midway through the second half when the Celtics suddenly evacuated their bench, unable to breathe. "Everybody started coughing," center Mark Blount said. "I felt like I was going to throw up, man." Paul E. Johnson, the NBA security official assigned to Boston, said police believe four men released a canister of pepper spray as a prank and then left the building. "Immediately after they left, the complaints started," he said. There was no odor, but players and fans reported problems with their throats and eyes. No one sought treatment at the FleetCenter's emergency medical station. Celtics coach Jim O'Brien wanted to cancel or postpone the rest of the game, but play resumed after a nine-minute delay when referee Hue Hollins decided that there was no danger. "We can't just arbitrarily say the game is over," he said. Even without Paul Pierce (sore back), the Celtics easily sent the Clippers to their second loss since Johnson was promoted to replace Alvin Gentry on Monday. Boston won for the fifth time in six games and swept Los Angeles for the third consecutive season. "Our guys refused to be distracted," O'Brien said. "They came back out and played good basketball." Corey Maggette scored 17 for the Clippers, who trailed by 10 after three quarters and never made it close after that. Quentin Richardson had 14 points and 10 rebounds. Johnson played for the Celtics from 1983-90, the fourth man to the Big Three of Larry Bird, Kevin McHale and Robert Parish that won two NBA titles. Johnson's No. 3 has been retired by the Celtics. Since getting promoted to interim coach on Monday, Johnson has heard from many of his former teammates and others from his Celtics days. What he hasn't done, though, is win. Johnson has 22 games left in his audition. And he'll conduct much of it without Elton Brand, who went on the injured list Friday with a stress fracture in his left leg. Also, center Michael Olowokandi is recovering from knee surgery. Lamar Odom played after missing two games with a sprained right ankle but went 3-for-17 from the floor. Richardson was 5-for-20. Game notes
Pierce missed the game because of the lingering pain of a sore back he hurt Feb. 22 when he slipped and fell on ice. The Celtics improved to 3-11 without him. ... Eric Piatkowski was a late scratch from the starting lineup. Corey Maggette started in his place. ... It wasn't Johnson's only NBA coaching experience. He was a Celtics assistant when head coach M.L. Carr decided to skip a game to attend a college combine on April 16, 1997. The Hornets won 108-102 despite Antoine Walker's first career triple-double. ... Wednesday's game against New Orleans is Red Auerbach bobblehead night. ... The Clippers activated Tremaine Fowlkes to replace Brand, who has missed the last six games.
